From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] networking: disable prefetch and preconnect by default

Chromium speculatively prefetches resources and pre-connects to origins
it predicts the user will visit. This leaks browsing intent to those
origins before the user navigates there.

This patch disables:
  - DNS prefetching (predicts navigation targets from the address bar)
  - Preconnect (opens TCP+TLS handshakes to predicted origins)
  - Link prefetch (<link rel="prefetch"> on pages)
  - Prerender (loads pages in background before navigation)
  - NetworkPrediction service

All four are disabled by default. Users can re-enable them individually
via Settings → Privacy → Predictive features.

PILLAR: Privacy / Transparency
JOURNAL: none — this patch prevents requests that would otherwise happen

---
 chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc | 12 +++++++++++-
 chrome/common/pref_names.cc             |  4 ++--
 chrome/common/pref_names.h              |  2 ++
 3 files changed, 15 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc b/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
index 3e4f5d6a..9b8c7d0e 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
@@ -415,6 +415,18 @@ void ProfileImpl::RegisterProfilePrefs(
   registry->RegisterBooleanPref(prefs::kNetworkPredictionEnabled,
-                                 true,
+                                 false,  // Fennec: off by default
                                  user_prefs::PrefRegistrySyncable::SYNCABLE_PREF);
+
+  // Fennec: disable all speculative network activity by default.
+  // Each can be re-enabled individually in Settings → Privacy.
+  registry->RegisterBooleanPref(prefs::kDnsPrefetchingEnabled, false);
+  registry->RegisterBooleanPref(prefs::kPreconnectEnabled, false);
+  registry->RegisterBooleanPref(prefs::kLinkPrefetchEnabled, false);
+  registry->RegisterBooleanPref(prefs::kPrerenderEnabled, false);
 }

diff --git a/chrome/common/pref_names.cc b/chrome/common/pref_names.cc
index 8a7b6c5d..1e2f3d4e 100644
--- a/chrome/common/pref_names.cc
+++ b/chrome/common/pref_names.cc
@@ -502,8 +502,8 @@ namespace prefs {
 // Whether DNS prefetching is enabled.
 const char kDnsPrefetchingEnabled[] = "net.dns_prefetching_enabled";

-// Default: true (Chromium default)
-// Fennec override: false — registered in ProfileImpl::RegisterProfilePrefs
+// Fennec default: false
+// Re-enable: Settings → Privacy → DNS prefetching

